02/04/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Dozens of suspected members of a Turkish extremist Marxist organisation were arrested in Turkey and four other countries on Thursday (1 April). 
Thirty-seven people were detained in Istanbul and 16 others in simultaneous police raids in Belgium, Germany, Italy and the Netherlands. 
They are suspected of belonging to the Revolutionary People's Liberation Party Front, which has been on the EU list of terrorist organisations since 2002. 
The group is blamed for the deaths of 100 policemen and soldiers and at least 80 civilians. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 02/04/04; AP, AFP - 01/04/04)
